    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 26-30.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - These verses contain last words respecting David's reign, its extent and its length; respecting his death and age, and the succession of Solomon; and respecting the sources of the history of himself, his reign, his people, and other countries. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 26.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The words of this verse, not indeed hard to follow here, but marking the close instead of the commencement or career of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "David's reign over all Israel",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", are paralleled by the earlier passage, ",
        "children": []
      },
